I confirmed this by building with bazel --config=android_arm64, unpacking the .APK, and using the file command (note the armeabi-v7a directory):

lib/armeabi-v7a/libtensorflowlite_jni.so: ELF 32-bit LSB  shared object, ARM, EABI5 version 1 (SYSV), dynamically linked, stripped

The internal version of the build with the same commands contains arm64-v8a/libtensorflowlite_jni.so, a 64-bit ELF file.

I'll check to see if there's an easy fix.

body:
I confirmed this by building with `bazel --config=android_arm64`, unpacking the .APK, and using the `file` command (note the armeabi-v7a directory):

```
lib/armeabi-v7a/libtensorflowlite_jni.so: ELF 32-bit LSB  shared object, ARM, EABI5 version 1 (SYSV), dynamically linked, stripped
```

The internal version of the build with the same commands contains `arm64-v8a/libtensorflowlite_jni.so`, a 64-bit ELF file.

I'll check to see if there's an easy fix.
